JOHANNESBURG - The banking sector says the recent downgrading of local banks will lower South Africa s creditworthiness, and make financing harder. The Banking Association of South Africa says while it expected Moody s recent decision, it adds further emphasis to the ongoing policy confusion and weak leadership in the country.Ratings agency Moody s downgraded deposit ratings of Standard Bank, First Rand, Absa, Nedbank and Investec.READ: Moody's downgrades top banksDespite having strong financial strength, the country s banks are seen to hold moderate credit risk.The association says South Africa s banking system remains fundamentally solid and respected in the world.It's also ready to partner with civil society, labour and government in turning the economy around.eNCA